      <mods:abstract>On December 1, 2008, the New York Daily News stole the iconic skyscraper by exploiting (and exposing) a legal loophole, through which some of the newspaper’s journalists were able to get the city to transfer the deeds of the tower to a fraudulent party using a forged notary stamp. The heist, one of the biggest of American history, took less than 90 minutes. The US$1.89 billion tower was returned within less than 24 hours. The 102-story Art Deco skyscraper is located on 350 Fifth Avenue Manhattan, New York.
